<p>I have a HashTable(System.Collection) and a custom property.</p>  <p>The default value of "_sendToDb" should be false, I will change this  later in the Grid of my wpf-program.</p>  <p>This is what I have:</p>  <p>My Hashtable:</p>  <pre><code>Hashtable hsh = new Hashtable(); </code></pre>  <p>My property:</p>  <pre><code>public class ImagesFromFS : INotifyPropertyChanged {      string _value;     string _path;     bool _sendToDb;     ...      public string Path     {         get         {             return _path;         }          set         {             _path = value;             onPropertyChanged();         }     }       public bool SendToDb     {         get         {             return _sendToDb;         }          set         {             onPropertyChanged();             _sendToDb = value;         }     }      public string Value     {         get         {             return _value;         }          set         {             _value = value;         }     } } </code></pre>  <p>The final goal should be, binding my new created property to the gridView.</p>